Create RAM DISK
# modprobe brd rd_size=19123456
...after this step /dev/ram0 exists.

You now can put a filesystem on it.

# mkfs /dev/ram0

# mount /dev/ram0 /mnt 
# df /mnt 
Filesystem           1K-blocks      Used Available Use% Mounted on
/dev/ram0               119539      1550    111817   2% /mnt
