--TEST SPEED WITH EXT3--

Go to where the filesystem you mounted is at:

# cd /mnt/r55

-WRITE TEST:-

ZEROS DATA:

 dd if=/dev/zero of=testfile0 bs=2k count=10; sync;
raid 5 2gb/s
raid 1 1gb/s
raid 5  903 MB/s
raid 5  709 MB/s


RANDOM DATA:

 dd if=/dev/urandom of=testfileR bs=1k count=10; sync;
raid 5 81920000 bytes (82 MB) copied, 6.61769 s, 12.4 MB/s
raid 1 81920000 bytes (82 MB) copied, 5.54717 s, 14.8 MB/s


 dd if=/dev/md3 of=test bs=64k count=16k conv=fdatasync

dd if=/dev/zero of=DEV bs=1k count=100
 (i.e., writing 10G in blocks of 100M).

All DATA will be erased
dd if=/dev/urandom of=/dev/sdb1 bs=4k count=10k
write test
dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/sdb bs=4k count=10k
read test
dd of=/dev/null if=/dev/sdb bs=4k count=10k
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
-READ TEST:-

ZEROS DATA:

# dd if=testfile0 of=/dev/null

RANDOM DATA:

dd if=testfileR of=/dev/null 

OTHER READ TEST:

# hdparm -Tt /dev/md3
RAID 1
 Timing cached reads:   23416 MB in  2.00 seconds = 11719.93 MB/sec
 Timing buffered disk reads: 494 MB in  3.01 seconds = 164.08 MB/sec


# hdparm -Tt --direct /dev/md3
RAID 1
 Timing O_DIRECT cached reads:   1030 MB in  2.00 seconds = 514.49 MB/sec
 Timing O_DIRECT disk reads: 492 MB in  3.01 seconds = 163.67 MB/sec


DONT FORGET TO REMOVE THE TEST FILES
# rm testfileR
# rm testfile0

