#####################################
http://serverfault.com/questions/461306/make-a-cronjob-wait-for-previous-rsync-job-to-finish

nano  crontab.txt
crontab crontab.txt

Create a cronjob for rsync
*/1   *    *    *    *   "job every minute"
10 * * * * echo “This command is run at 10 min past every hour”
22 7 * * * echo “This command is run daily at 7:22 am”
22 20 * * * echo “This command is run daily at 8:22 pm”

nano crontab.txt 
22 7 * * *  rsync -avz --append --delete /data/lib/mysql /hdd/lib/
1 * * * *  rsync -avz --append --delete /data/lib/mysql /hdd/lib/

1 * * * *  pgrep -c rsync || rsync -avz --append --delete  /data/lib/mysql /hdd/lib/

OR

1 * * * * pgrep -c rsync || rsync --append --delete  --recursive  /data/lib/mysql /hdd/lib/
@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@
Invoke crontab to set your cron job
From the shell command line, go to where you uploaded your crontab.txt file. 

nano /hdd/etc/crontab.txt



