Numa and swaping for DUAL cpus MYSQL
http://blog.jcole.us/2010/09/28/mysql-swap-insanity-and-the-numa-architecture/
An easy solution to this is to interleave the allocated memory. It is possible to do this using numactl as described above:

 numactl --interleave all 
nano /usr/bin/mysqld_safe  , adding the following line (after cmd="$NOHUP_NICENESS"), which prefixes the command to start mysqld with a call to numactl:

find: Launch mysqld with numactl.
put this after
cmd="/usr/bin/numactl --interleave all $cmd"
